<h1>CheckPoint SNX (SSL VPN)</h1>

<p>Experimental support for <a href="https://www.checkpoint.com/quantum/remote-access-vpn/">SSL VPN</a>
was added to OpenConnect in June 2021. </p>

<p>CheckPoint mode is requested by adding <tt>--protocol=checkpoint</tt>
to the command line:
<pre>
  openconnect --protocol=checkpoint snx.example.com
</pre></p>

<h2>Quirks and Issues</h2>

<p>Currently, OpenConnect supports basic username and password, PinPad, KeyFob,
    Challenge and certificate-based authentication. Mobile Access mode is a WIP.</p>

<p>Please, do not specify any path part of the server URL. It is not supported in basic SNX mode.</p>

<p>VPN features support is summarized in table below.</p>
<table dir="auto" border="1">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Client type</th>
            <th>Authentication</th>
            <th>Two-Factor auth.</th>
            <th>Configuration</th>
            <th>Transport</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>snx client (Linux)</td>
            <td>HTTP (+)</td>
            <td align="center">unavailable</td>
            <td>SNX (+)</td>
            <td>SNX (+)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Mobile (Web) Access</td>
            <td>HTTP (*)</td>
            <td align="center">*</td>
            <td>SNX (+)</td>
            <td>SNX (+)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Mobile devices (Android, iOS)</td>
            <td>HTTP (*)</td>
            <td align="center">*</td>
            <td>HTTP (*)</td>
            <td>ESP (*)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>SecuRemote, Endpoint Security etc. (desktop)</td>
            <td>IKE (-)</td>
            <td align="center">-</td>
            <td>IKE (-)</td>
            <td>ESP (*)</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<p>+ - feature supported.</p>
<p>* - feature support is WIP(work in progress).</p>
<p>- - feature not supported.</p>
